$interpreted: : Three years ago...
Tingko: It's really nice out, today~
Tindoiimu: It's been a long time since I've been out on a walk. Butter seems happy, too.
Qilin Guard: Damn slave! You're getting that filthy water all over me!
Jiyanama: I'm very sorry... it's too heavy, I couldn't hold it steady...
Qilin Guard: I just bought these shoes, too! Now how're you gonna repay me!?
Jiyanama: How about I clean them up for you?
Qilin Guard: Yuck, like I'd let some stinking bug anywhere near these fresh kicks!
Qilin Guard: Jeez, as if this post weren't crap enough already, now my shoes are ruined... Get the heck outta here, maggot!
Tindoiimu: Let go of her!
Tingko: Jiyanama, are you alright?
Tindoiimu: Picking on an old woman with no way to defend herself? Is this how you treat your guests?
Qilin Guard: Hmph... You're a hostage, so we can't touch you. Doesn't mean this random old maggot is off limits!
Qilin Guard: She's the one who couldn't hold a damn water bucket! Don't you bugs know any manners?
Tindoiimu: ...And hasn't the qilin chieftain taught you any manners of your own?
Qilin Guard: Hey! You talkin' bad about Qing Feng!?
Qing-Feng: What's all this racket?
Qilin Guard: C-Chieftain Qing Feng! They... They started it, and---
Qing-Feng: You're a disgrace. Get out of my sight.
Qing-Feng: My servant seems to have mistreated you, Princess. I will handle him.
Qing-Feng: That said... you are a hostage. Perhaps, for your safety, I should restrict these little walks you take.
Qing-Feng: These sort of things wouldn't happen if you just stayed inside.
Tindoiimu: ...I never wished to start any trouble, I just wish those guards would treat my nanny with moreâ€”
Tingko: Jiyanama, I already cleaned that this morning.
Jiyanama: ......
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, come have some tea with us. Take a break.
Jiyanama: ......
Tingko: Jiyanama hasn't been herself for the past few days...
Tindoiimu: You think it's because of what happened with the guards?
Tingko: Hmm... I have noticed she's been extra nice to them lately.
Tingko: She's even been giving them wine and snacks... She must be really worked up from last time.
Tindoiimu: I really wish she would perk up a little bit...
Tingko: Princess, did you forget? Next month is Jiyanama's---
Tindoiimu: It's Jiyanama's birthday!
Tingko: How about we get her a present? That would definitely cheer her up a bit!
Tindoiimu: A present... what do you think she would like?
Tingko: I'm sure she'd love whatever you pick for her. Let's buy something when we go out shopping in a few days.
Tindoiimu: Shopping... But, if we go out together, what if something happens again?
Tingko: Hmm... Well, your clothes do attract a bit of attention. And we'd have to get past those guards, too.
Tingko: Oh~!
Tingko: I've got an idea! Don't worry, Princess, Just leave it to me and I'll make it great!
Tindoiimu: (Don't worry? Make it great...? Alright, now I am a little worried...)
